 A SHA-256 rule compares the complete file digest. A pattern rule performs a bounded linear byte search over a file no larger than the existing ZenovFS1 64 KiB slot. Maximum rules and maximum pattern size are fixed, preventing unbounded regex, decompression or recursive-parser work inside the kernel.
 
+## On-access read mediation
+
+Ordinary user-visible reads are classified after ZenovFS checksum verification and before bytes are returned to the shell or a ring-3 file-read caller. `INFECTED` denies the read, zeroes the already-filled destination bytes and resets the returned size. `SUSPICIOUS` is allowed only after a durable `READ-AUDIT` record succeeds. A read block records `READ-BLOCK` but does not mutate or automatically quarantine the source.
+
+Internal `/security`, `/repo`, `/var/lib/zenpkg` and `/quarantine` reads remain on their dedicated raw verification paths to avoid enforcement recursion. This exclusion does not bypass executable appraisal, signed-policy validation or protected-path mutation controls. The full contract is documented in [`ON_ACCESS_PROTECTION_0.1.1.md`](ON_ACCESS_PROTECTION_0.1.1.md).
